Prep

# UTF-8 sanitation (safe for stringi versions)
sanitize_utf8 <- function(x) {
  stringi::stri_enc_toutf8(x, is_unknown_8bit = TRUE)
}

# ASCII transliteration (print safe)
force_ascii <- function(x) {
  iconv(x, from = "", to = "ASCII//TRANSLIT", sub = "")
}

API Search function

# Inputs:
#   query     : Character string containing the search query
#   offset    : Integer offset for pagination (default = 0)
#   limit     : Maximum number of records to return per request ( 100)
#   year_min  : Earliest publication year to include
#   year_max  : Latest publication year to include

search_semantic_scholar <- function(query,
                                    offset   = 0,
                                    limit    = 100,
                                    year_min = 2000,
                                    year_max = 2025) {

  # Construct API Request Function
  # Wrap in tryCatch() to prevent hard failures during knitting
  resp <- tryCatch(
    {
      request("https://api.semanticscholar.org/graph/v1/paper/search") |>
        # Attach query parameters to the request URL
        req_url_query(
          query  = query,
          offset = offset,
          limit  = limit,

          # Explicitly request only required fields to reduce payload size
          fields = paste(
            c(
              "title",
              "authors.name",
              "year",
              "citationCount",
              "url"
            ),
            collapse = ","
          ),

          # Restrict results to a specified publication years
          year = paste0(year_min, "-", year_max)
        ) |>
        # Execute the HTTP request
        req_perform() |>
        # Parse JSON response body into an R list
        resp_body_json()
    },
    # On any request or parsing error, return NULL
    error = function(e) return(NULL)
  )

  # Return an empty tibble if no data are present
  if (is.null(resp) || length(resp$data) == 0) {
    return(tibble())
  }
      
  # Extract and normalize fields into a tidy tibble
  tibble(
    
    # Paper title (UTF-8 sanitized)
    title = sanitize_utf8(
      map_chr(resp$data, "title", .default = NA_character_)
    ),

    # Author names collapsed into a single comma-separated string
    authors = sanitize_utf8(
      map_chr(
        resp$data,
        ~ paste(map_chr(.x$authors, "name"), collapse = ", "),
        .default = NA_character_
      )
    ),

    # Publication year
    year = map_int(resp$data, "year", .default = NA_integer_),

    # Citation count as reported by Semantic Scholar
    citations = map_int(resp$data, "citationCount", .default = NA_integer_),

    # Semantic Scholar  URL
    link = map_chr(resp$data, "url", .default = NA_character_)
  )
}

Pagination

# Paced to avoid 429 error
offsets <- seq(0, 500, by = 100)

queries <- c("disinformation", "misinformation")

results_raw <- map_dfr(
  queries,
  function(q) {
    map_dfr(
      offsets,
      function(o) {
        Sys.sleep(runif(1, 1.5, 3))
        search_semantic_scholar(
          query = q,
          offset = o,
          year_min = 2000,
          year_max = 2025
        )
      }
    )
  }
) |>
  distinct(title, year, .keep_all = TRUE)

Text Hardening

# Prevents gsub crashes
results_raw <- results_raw |>
  mutate(
    title = force_ascii(
      stringi::stri_replace_all_charclass(
        title,
        "[^[:print:]]",
        ""
      )
    ),
    authors = force_ascii(
      stringi::stri_replace_all_charclass(
        authors,
        "[^[:print:]]",
        ""
      )
    )
  )

allintitle Filtering

# Requires 'disinformation' or 'misinformation' in the title 
results <- results_raw |>
  filter(
    stringi::stri_detect_regex(
      title,
      "(?i)disinformation|misinformation"
    )
  ) |>
  distinct(title, year, .keep_all = TRUE) |>
  arrange(desc(citations))

Output 2

# Output 2:
#   A table with one row per year and columns:
#     - Year
#     - Articles with 'Disinformation' in Title
#     - Articles with 'Misinformation' in Title
#     - Total Articles

article_counts <- results %>%
  mutate(
    has_disinfo = str_detect(str_to_lower(title), "disinformation"),
    has_misinfo = str_detect(str_to_lower(title), "misinformation")
  ) %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarise(
    disinformation_titles = sum(has_disinfo, na.rm = TRUE),
    misinformation_titles = sum(has_misinfo, na.rm = TRUE),
    total_titles = n(),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) %>%
  arrange(year)

article_counts_dt <- article_counts %>%
  dplyr::select(
    year,
    disinformation_titles,
    misinformation_titles,
    total_titles
  ) %>%
  as.data.frame()

DT::datatable(
  article_counts_dt,
  rownames = FALSE,
  options = list(
    pageLength = 15,
    autoWidth = TRUE,
    order = list(list(0, "desc")),  # sort by Year descending
    dom = "Bfrtip",
    buttons = c("copy", "csv", "excel"),
    columnDefs = list(
      list(className = "dt-center", targets = "_all")
    )
  ),
  colnames = c(
    "Year",
    "Articles with 'Disinformation' in Title",
    "Articles with 'Misinformation' in Title",
    "Total Articles"
  )
)

Output 2

# Output 2:
#   A table with one row per paper and columns:
#     - title
#     - authors (comma-separated string)
#     - year
#     - citation count
#     - Semantic Scholar URL

results_display <- results |>
  arrange(desc(citations)) |>
  mutate(
    link = sprintf('<a href="%s" target="_blank">link</a>', link)
  )
# Table construction
DT::datatable(
  results_display,
  escape = FALSE,
  rownames = FALSE,
  options = list(
    autoWidth = FALSE,
    columnDefs = list(
      list(width = "450px", targets = "title"),
      list(width = "80px",  targets = "link")
    )
  )
)
